<h3>Curriculum</h3>
<p>EMBA classes meet primarily three Saturdays and one Friday per month, 8 a.m.-5 p.m., at the Executive Development Center’s state-of-the-art downtown facility. The 39 credit-hour curriculum comprises five sessions over a 19-month period. The program includes a week-long international residency, which provides students with an enlightening global business perspective. Click  to see the class schedule for cohort starting in January 2014.</p>
<p>The leadership-relevant curriculum provides students with cross-functional business knowledge and encourages application of new theories and principles in real-world situations. The exchange of ideas stemming from participants’ professional experiences is an integral part of the learning process.</p>
<p>View a list of courses currently taught in the EMBA.</p>
</div>
